page.title: 01WILDFLOWERS IN NEWTONMORE 1
page.content:
The village of Newtonmore is situated in an upland valley with the fast flowing river Spey forming the eastern boundary of the Golf Course which formed the territory of our survey. The course is 244m. above sea level. The following flowering plants were identified and are coded as follows:
1.Daisy, 2.Coltsfoot, 3.Dandielion, 4.Lesser Celandine, 5.Wood Anemone, 6.Marsh Marigold, 7.Common Whitlow Grass, 8.Ivy-Leaved Crowfoot, 9.Petty Whin, 10.Lady's Mantle, 11.Slender Speedwell 12.Bitter Vetchling, 13.Broom, 14.Common Dog Violet, 15.Marsh Violet, 16.Wild Pansy, 17.Moutain Everlasting, 18.Red Veined Dandielion, 19.Ribwort Plantain, 20.Ivy-Leaved Speedwell, 21.Mouse Eared Chickweed,
